---
/**
 * Latency hiding animation: GPU warps interleave compute and memory stalls,
 * vs CPU core that just stalls.
 */
---

<figure class="latency-hiding">
  <div class="lh-grid">
    <!-- CPU side -->
    <div class="lh-col">
      <div class="lh-title">CPU — single core</div>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 320 110" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <text x="8" y="18" class="lane-label">Core 0</text>

        <!-- Timeline -->
        <rect x="55" y="8" width="50" height="18" rx="3" class="compute" />
        <text x="80" y="20" class="block-text">work</text>

        <rect x="105" y="8" width="90" height="18" rx="3" class="stall" />
        <text x="150" y="20" class="block-text stall-text">STALL (RAM ~100ns)</text>

        <rect x="195" y="8" width="50" height="18" rx="3" class="compute" />
        <text x="220" y="20" class="block-text">work</text>

        <rect x="245" y="8" width="65" height="18" rx="3" class="stall" />
        <text x="277" y="20" class="block-text stall-text">STALL</text>

        <!-- Utilization bar -->
        <text x="160" y="48" class="util-label">Core utilization</text>
        <rect x="55" y="54" width="255" height="12" rx="3" class="bar-bg" />
        <rect x="55" y="54" width="100" height="12" rx="3" class="bar-fill cpu-util" />
        <text x="182" y="63" class="bar-pct">~40%</text>

        <text x="160" y="90" class="takeaway">❌ Core idles during memory stalls</text>
        <text x="160" y="104" class="takeaway">Solution: bigger caches, prefetching</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- GPU side -->
    <div class="lh-col">
      <div class="lh-title">GPU — warp scheduling</div>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 320 140" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <!-- Arrow showing switching -->
        <text x="160" y="10" class="switch-label">← SM switches warps, always has work →</text>

        <!-- Warp timelines -->
        {Array.from({ length: 4 }).map((_, w) => (
          <g>
            <text x="4" y={30 + w * 20} class="lane-label">{`W${w}`}</text>
            {/* Alternating compute/wait blocks, offset per warp */}
            <rect x={55 + w * 30} y={20 + w * 20} width="40" height="14" rx="3" class="compute" />
            <rect x={95 + w * 30} y={20 + w * 20} width="70" height="14" rx="3" class="mem-wait" />
            <rect x={165 + w * 30} y={20 + w * 20} width="40" height="14" rx="3" class="compute" />
          </g>
        ))}

        <!-- SM utilization bar -->
        <text x="160" y="112" class="util-label">SM utilization</text>
        <rect x="55" y="118" width="255" height="12" rx="3" class="bar-bg" />
        <rect x="55" y="118" width="245" height="12" rx="3" class="bar-fill gpu-util" />
        <text x="182" y="127" class="bar-pct">~95%</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>
  <figcaption>The CPU stalls on cache misses. The GPU hides latency by switching between warps — while one waits for memory, another computes. With enough warps (<strong>occupancy</strong>), the SM is never idle.</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .latency-hiding {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .latency-hiding figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #888;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .lh-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 650px) {
    .lh-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .lh-col svg {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }
  .lh-title {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    color: #333;
  }
  .lane-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    fill: #888;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .compute {
    fill: #c8e6c9;
    stroke: #4caf50;
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .stall {
    fill: #ffcdd2;
    stroke: #e57373;
    stroke-width: 1;
    stroke-dasharray: 4 2;
  }
  .mem-wait {
    fill: #fff3e0;
    stroke: #ffb74d;
    stroke-width: 1;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }
  .block-text {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 7px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #333;
  }
  .stall-text { fill: #c62828; }
  .switch-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 7px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #2e7d32;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .util-label {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 7.5px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #888;
  }
  .bar-bg {
    fill: #eee;
    stroke: #ddd;
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .bar-fill {
    stroke: none;
  }
  .cpu-util { fill: #e57373; }
  .gpu-util { fill: #81c784; }
  .bar-pct {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #444;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .takeaway {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    text-anchor: middle;
    fill: #888;
  }
</style>
